<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.837/303</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Marseilles</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gaulin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marseilles</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-23">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <persName>Mitchell John Kennedy</persName>, claiming American
                                citizenship, resident Northfield, Vt., made affidavit stating was
                                fireman British steamer <hi rend="italic">Mohacsfield</hi> which
                                sailed November last [from] Newport News, Va., for Italy carrying
                                wheat. Attacked and reported sunk by submarine, unknown nationality,
                                about January 13, thirteen miles off Malta. Vessel flying British
                                flag when attacked. Had small gun which witness believes was used
                                while attempting escape. Crew given 30 minutes take boats. Remained
                                boats 23 hours. Weather stormy, sea rough, no vessels vicinity.
                                Vessel not transport. Witness did not see ship sink. Only American
                                aboard. Four casualties including two killed. Officers not landed
                                here.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gaulin</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>